Death toll rises to 217 in SE Turkey quake: interior minister
2011-10-24 07:41:50 GMT
ANKARA, Oct. 25 (Xinhua) -- The death toll from the powerful earthquake in southeast Turkey has risen to 217 and the number of the injured to 1,090, Interior Minister Idris Naim Sahin said Monday.Sahin said that Sunday's 7.2-magnitude quake left 100 people dead in the city of Van and another 117 dead in the worst-hit town of Ercis.Sahin, who is in charge of emergency operations in Ercis, said a total of 1,090 people were known to have been injured.Local media reports said earlier that the death toll was expected to rise as hundreds remain unaccounted for.
